@startuml rrwm-loop
' RRWM online weighted-majority update loop (Cortes et al. 2015, Fig. 6).
' Each round: predict by sampling Wₜ₋₁, observe a loss transducer Vₜ, compose,
' weight-push to restore a stochastic automaton. Deep-learning purple for the
' learner; algorithms-green for the WFST ops it drives. Palette: docs/diagrams/README.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #607D8B
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #E1BEE7
  BorderColor #6A1B9A
  FontColor #102027
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF59D
  DiamondBorderColor #F9A825
  DiamondFontColor #5D4037
}

title <b>RRWM online learning loop</b>\n<size:11><i>cumulative automaton Wₜ over the η-power semiring; regret E[R_T] ≤ 2M√(T log N)</i></size>

start
:**W₀** ← one-state automaton\n(all paths weight 1̄);
repeat
  #E1BEE7:**predict** ŷₜ ~ Wₜ₋₁\n(sample ∝ weight);
  :observe outcome yₜ\nbuild loss transducer **Vₜ**;
  #C8E6C9:**compose**  Wₜ ← Wₜ₋₁ ∘ Vₜ\n(combine all path experts);
  #C8E6C9:**weight-push**  Wₜ ← push(Wₜ)\n(restore stochastic: out-weights sum to 1̄);
  :accumulate loss ℓ(ŷₜ, yₜ);
repeat while (round < T  and  states < max_rounds?) is (yes)
->no\n(reset Wₜ ← W₀ if cap hit);
:return W_T\n(learned expert weighting);
stop

legend right
  | Step | Operation |
  |<#E1BEE7> predict | sample path from Wₜ₋₁ |
  | observe | construct Vₜ from loss |
  |<#C8E6C9> compose | Wₜ₋₁ ∘ Vₜ |
  |<#C8E6C9> push | make stochastic for next sample |
endlegend
@enduml
